{"type":"message","id":"fdcb9176","parentId":"79e30247","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:54:44.460Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_tos6u8f597xi_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 125415\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: and (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and insights:\r\n\r\n1. **CFI Compression Experiment completed** - we have a three-dimensional filter: CFI � 0.5 AND freq � 3 AND freq < 120\r\n2. **Next pending action**: \"Hybrid CFIxFreq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\"\r\n3. **Key insight**: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nThe next logical step is to implement the hybrid scoring experiment that combines CFI and frequency multiplicatively rather than using binary thresholds.\r\n\r\nThis would involve:\r\n1. Creating a new experiment script that calculates the hybrid score\r\n2. Testing it against the same 200 pulses\r\n3. Comparing results to the previous CFI-only and freq-only approaches\r\n\r\nLet me create the experimental script for Strategy C - the hybrid CFIxFreq scoring approach.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression experiment identified that three-dimensional filtering (CFI � 0.5 AND freq ? [3, 120)) is better than binary thresholds, but Strategy C (hybrid scoring) hasn't been tested yet. The proposed score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120) could better distinguish constant-format tokens from research trajectories.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nImplement Strategy C hybrid scoring experiment - create the analysis script that tests CFI x sqrt(freq) scoring against the same 200-pulse corpus to see if it better isolates meaningful research tokens from metaprogramming artifacts.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Strategy C: Hybrid CFIxFreq^0.5 Scoring Experiment\r\n# Testing: score(T) = CFI(T) x �(freq(T)/120) for token significance\r\n\r\n$script_start = Get-Date\r\n$pulse_dir = \"pulses\"\r\n$output_file = \"research/STRATEGY_C_HYBRID_SCORING.md\"\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== Strategy C: Hybrid CFIxFreq^0.5 Scoring Experiment ===\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Hypothesis: Multiplicative scoring distinguishes constant-format from research trajectory better than thresholds\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# Load pulse corpus\r\n$pulse_files = @()\r\nGet-ChildItem $pulse_dir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Where-Object { $_.Name -match \"^\\d{8}_\\d{6}\" } | ForEach-Object {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $_.FullName -Raw\r\n    $tokens = [regex]::Matches($content, '\\S+') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\r\n    $pulse_files += @{\r\n        File = $_.Name\r\n        Tokens = $tokens\r\n    }\r\n}\r\nWrite-Host \"Loaded $($pulse_files.Count) pulses\"\r\n\r\n# Count tokens across all pulses\r\n$token_stats = @{}\r\nforeach ($pf in $pulse_files) {\r\n    $seen = @{}\r\n    foreach ($tok in $pf.Tokens) {\r\n        if (-not $seen.ContainsKey($tok)) {\r\n            $seen[$tok] = $true\r\n            if ($token_stats.ContainsKey($tok)) {\r\n                $token_stats[$tok].Count++\r\n            } else {\r\n                $token_stats[$tok] = @{\r\n                    Token = $tok\r\n                    Count = 1\r\n                }\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Calculate CFI and hybrid score for each token\r\n$token_analysis = @()\r\n$total_pulses = $pulse_files.Count\r\n\r\nforeach ($entry in $token_stats.Values) {\r\n    $freq = $entry.Count\r\n    $cfi = [Math]::Round($freq / $total_pulses, 4)\r\n    \r\n    # Strategy C: Hybrid score = CFI x �(freq/120)\r\n    # Clamped: max freq considered = 120 (beyond that, frequency adds no more value)\r\n    $freq_factor = [Math]::Min(1.0, $freq / 120.0)\r\n    $hybrid_score = [Math]::Round($cfi * [Math]::Sqrt($freq_factor), 4)\r\n    \r\n    $token_analysis += @{\r\n        Token = $entry.Token\r\n        Freq = $freq\r\n        CFI = $cfi\r\n        HybridScore = $hybrid_score\r\n        IsResearch = ($cfi -ge 0.5 -and $freq -ge 3 -and $freq -lt 120)\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Sort by hybrid score descending\r\n$token_analysis = $token_analysis | Sort-Object -Descending { $_.HybridScore }\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Token analysis complete: $($token_analysis.Count) unique tokens\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# Analyze results\r\n$high_cfi_high_freq = $token_analysis | Where-Object { $_.CFI -ge 0.7 -and $_.Freq -ge 100 }\r\n$high_cfi_med_freq = $token_analysis | Where-Object { $_.CFI -ge 0.5 -and $_.Freq -ge 3 -and $_.Freq -lt 120 }\r\n$high_hybrid_only = $token_analysis | Where-Object { $_.HybridScore -ge 0.3 -and ($_.CFI -lt 0.5 -or $_.Freq -lt 3) }\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== Strategy C Results ===\"\r\nWrite-Host \"High CFI + High Freq (likely constant-format): $($high_cfi_high_freq.Count)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"High CFI + Med Freq (research trajectory): $($high_cfi_med_freq.Count)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"High Hybrid Score (but low CFI/freq): $($high_hybrid_only.Count)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# Show top 20 by hybrid score\r\nWrite-Host \"Top 20 tokens by Hybrid Score:\"\r\n$token_analysis[0..19] | ForEach\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 12:54:36"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":669,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 125415\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: and (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and insights:\r\n\r\n1. **CFI Compression Experiment completed** - we have a three-dimensional filter: CFI � 0.5 AND freq � 3 AND freq < 120\r\n2. **Next pending action**: \"Hybrid CFIxFreq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\"\r\n3. **Key insight**: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nThe next logical step is to implement the hybrid scoring experiment that combines CFI and frequency multiplicatively rather than using binary thresholds.\r\n\r\nThis would involve:\r\n1. Creating a new experiment script that calculates the hybrid score\r\n2. Testing it against the same 200 pulses\r\n3. Comparing results to the previous CFI-only and freq-only approaches\r\n\r\nLet me create the experimental script for Strategy C - the hybrid CFIxFreq scoring approach.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression experiment identified that three-dimensional filtering (CFI � 0.5 AND freq ? [3, 120)) is better than binary thresholds, but Strategy C (hybrid scoring) hasn't been tested yet. The proposed score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120) could better distinguish constant-format tokens from research trajectories.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nImplement Strategy C hybrid scoring experiment - create the analysis script that tests CFI x sqrt(freq) scoring against the same 200-pulse corpus to see if it better isolates meaningful research tokens from metaprogramming artifacts.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Strategy C: Hybrid CFIxFreq^0.5 Scoring Experiment\r\n# Testing: score(T) = CFI(T) x �(freq(T)/120) for token significance\r\n\r\n$script_start = Get-Date\r\n$pulse_dir = \"pulses\"\r\n$output_file = \"research/STRATEGY_C_HYBRID_SCORING.md\"\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== Strategy C: Hybrid CFIxFreq^0.5 Scoring Experiment ===\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Hypothesis: Multiplicative scoring distinguishes constant-format from research trajectory better than thresholds\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# Load pulse corpus\r\n$pulse_files = @()\r\nGet-ChildItem $pulse_dir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Where-Object { $_.Name -match \"^\\d{8}_\\d{6}\" } | ForEach-Object {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $_.FullName -Raw\r\n    $tokens = [regex]::Matches($content, '\\S+') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\r\n    $pulse_files += @{\r\n        File = $_.Name\r\n        Tokens = $tokens\r\n    }\r\n}\r\nWrite-Host \"Loaded $($pulse_files.Count) pulses\"\r\n\r\n# Count tokens across all pulses\r\n$token_stats = @{}\r\nforeach ($pf in $pulse_files) {\r\n    $seen = @{}\r\n    foreach ($tok in $pf.Tokens) {\r\n        if (-not $seen.ContainsKey($tok)) {\r\n            $seen[$tok] = $true\r\n            if ($token_stats.ContainsKey($tok)) {\r\n                $token_stats[$tok].Count++\r\n            } else {\r\n                $token_stats[$tok] = @{\r\n                    Token = $tok\r\n                    Count = 1\r\n                }\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Calculate CFI and hybrid score for each token\r\n$token_analysis = @()\r\n$total_pulses = $pulse_files.Count\r\n\r\nforeach ($entry in $token_stats.Values) {\r\n    $freq = $entry.Count\r\n    $cfi = [Math]::Round($freq / $total_pulses, 4)\r\n    \r\n    # Strategy C: Hybrid score = CFI x �(freq/120)\r\n    # Clamped: max freq considered = 120 (beyond that, frequency adds no more value)\r\n    $freq_factor = [Math]::Min(1.0, $freq / 120.0)\r\n    $hybrid_score = [Math]::Round($cfi * [Math]::Sqrt($freq_factor), 4)\r\n    \r\n    $token_analysis += @{\r\n        Token = $entry.Token\r\n        Freq = $freq\r\n        CFI = $cfi\r\n        HybridScore = $hybrid_score\r\n        IsResearch = ($cfi -ge 0.5 -and $freq -ge 3 -and $freq -lt 120)\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Sort by hybrid score descending\r\n$token_analysis = $token_analysis | Sort-Object -Descending { $_.HybridScore }\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Token analysis complete: $($token_analysis.Count) unique tokens\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# Analyze results\r\n$high_cfi_high_freq = $token_analysis | Where-Object { $_.CFI -ge 0.7 -and $_.Freq -ge 100 }\r\n$high_cfi_med_freq = $token_analysis | Where-Object { $_.CFI -ge 0.5 -and $_.Freq -ge 3 -and $_.Freq -lt 120 }\r\n$high_hybrid_only = $token_analysis | Where-Object { $_.HybridScore -ge 0.3 -and ($_.CFI -lt 0.5 -or $_.Freq -lt 3) }\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== Strategy C Results ===\"\r\nWrite-Host \"High CFI + High Freq (likely constant-format): $($high_cfi_high_freq.Count)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"High CFI + Med Freq (research trajectory): $($high_cfi_med_freq.Count)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"High Hybrid Score (but low CFI/freq): $($high_hybrid_only.Count)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# Show top 20 by hybrid score\r\nWrite-Host \"Top 20 tokens by Hybrid Score:\"\r\n$token_analysis[0..19] | ForEach\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 12:54:36","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774371284459}}
