{"type":"message","id":"f4652450","parentId":"be5b1b0e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:54:54.959Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_g6gktkrh6j1x_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 4576\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2986\n[mutation parse failed] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2986\n[master 122880e] pulse: 2026-03-24 125415\n 5 files changed, 215 insertions(+), 80 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 125415.md\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 125316.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 125415 - The CFI compression experiment identified that three-dimensional filtering (CFI � 0.5 AND freq ? [3, 120)) is better than binary thresholds, but Strategy C (hybrid scoring) hasn't been tested yet. The proposed score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120) could better distinguish constant-format tokens from research trajectories."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"cool-willow","total":8,"totalLines":8,"totalChars":755,"truncated":false,"exitCode":0,"name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774371294957}}
